         <abstract>
            <p>Red, yellow, and green traffic lights direct traffic through intersections, indicate certain conditions, and assure motorists of safe passage. Unfortunately for water operators, colors observed during water sample testing usually require further interpretation. In particular, when checking for orthophosphate (OP) residuals, blue may lead to false assumptions.</p>
